-Holland, Amsterdam.  American Elsevier, New York.\n* [[John Corcoran (logician)|Corcoran, John]], and [[Jos\u00e9 Miguel Sag\u00fcillo|Sag\u00fcillo, Jos\u00e9 Miguel]], 2011. \"The Absence of Multiple Universes of Discourse in the 1936 Tarski Consequence-Definition Paper\", ''History and Philosophy of Logic 32'': 359\u201380. [http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/01445340.2011.577145#.UksmOD_-kQs]\n* Corcoran, John, and Weber, Leonardo, 2015. \"Tarski\u2019s convention T: condition beta\", South American Journal of Logic. 1, 3\u201332.\n* [[John Etchemendy|Etchemendy, John]], 1999. ''The Concept of Logical Consequence''. Stanford CA: CSLI Publications. {{isbn|1-57586-194-1}}\n* {{cite journal | author = Feferman Solomon | authorlink = Solomon Feferman | year = 1999 | title = Logic, Logics, and Logicism | url = http://math.stanford.edu/~feferman/papers/logiclogicism.pdf | journal = Notre Dame Journal of Formal Logic | volume = 40 | issue = | pages = 31\u201354 | doi=10.1305/ndjfl/1039096304}}\n* [[Ivor Grattan-Guinness|Grattan-Guinness, Ivor]], 2000. ''The Search for Mathematical Roots 1870-1940''. Princeton Uni. Press.\n* Kirkham, Richard, 1992. ''Theories of Truth''. MIT Press.\n* [[Roger Maddux|Maddux, Roger D.]], 2006. ''Relation Algebras'', vol. 150 in \"Studies in Logic and the Foundations of Mathematics\", Elsevier Science.\n* {{cite journal | author = Mautner F. I. | authorlink = Friederich Ignaz Mautner | year = 1946 | title = An Extension of Klein's Erlanger Program: Logic as Invariant-Theory | url = | journal = American Journal of Mathematics | volume = 68 | issue = 3| pages = 345\u201384 | doi=10.2307/2371821| jstor = 2371821 }}\n* {{cite journal | author = McGee Van | year = 1996 | title = Logical Operations | url = | journal = Journal of Philosophical Logic | volume = 25 | issue = 6| pages = 567\u201380 | doi=10.1007/bf00265253}}\n* [[Karl Popper|Popper, Karl R.]], 1972, Rev. Ed. 1979, \"Philosophical Comments on Tarski's Theory of Truth\", with