{"title_page": "2003 Women's European Water Polo Championship", "text_new": "The '''[[European Water Polo Championship|2003 Women's European Water Polo Championship]]''' was the tenth edition of the bi-annual event, organised by the Europe's governing body in aquatics, the [[Ligue Europ\u00e9enne de Natation]]. The event took place in [[Ljubljana, Slovenia]] from June 7 to June 14, 2003.\n\nThere were two [[2003 Women's European Water Polo Championship Qualifier|qualification tournaments]] ahead of the event, held from April 11 to April 13, 2003 in [[Hamburg, Germany]] (with Greece, Germany, France, and Ukraine competing) and [[Eindhoven]], [[Netherlands]] (Netherlands, Spain, Czech Republic and Great Britain).\n\n==Qualification==\n*{{further|2003 Women's European Water Polo Championship Qualifier}}\n\n==Teams==\n{{col-begin-small}}\n{{col-2}}\n;GROUP A\n*{{wpw|GRE}} \n*{{wpw|GER}} \n*{{wpw|ITA}}\n*{{wpw|RUS}} \n{{col-2}}\n;GROUP B\n*{{wpw|HUN}} \n*{{wpw|NED}} \n*{{wpw|SLO}} \n*{{wpw|ESP}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Preliminary round==\n\n===GROUP A===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#DCDCDC\"\n!width=\"25\" |\n!width=\"200\"|Team\n!width=\"60\"|Points\n!width=\"60\"|G\n!width=\"60\"|W\n!width=\"60\"|D\n!width=\"60\"|L\n!width=\"60\"|GF\n!width=\"60\"|GA\n!width=\"60\"|Diff\n|- bgcolor=#AAFFAA\n|1.\n|align=left|{{wpw|ITA}}\n|'''6'''||3||3||0||0||33||24||+9\n|- bgcolor=#CCFFCC\n|2.\n|align=left|{{wpw|RUS}}\n|'''4'''||3||2||0||1||30||27||+3\n|- bgcolor=#CCFFCC\n|3.\n|align=left|{{wpw|GRE}}\n|'''2'''||3||1||0||2||16||20||\u22124\n|-\n|4.\n|align=left|{{wpw|GER}}\n|'''0'''||3||0||0||3||22||30||\u22128\n|}\n\n===GROUP B===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#DCDCDC\"\n!width=\"25\" |\n!width=\"200\"|Team\n!width=\"60\"|Points\n!width=\"60\"|G\n!width=\"60\"|W\n!width=\"60\"|D\n!width=\"60\"|L\n!width=\"60\"|GF\n!width=\"60\"|GA\n!width=\"60\"|Diff\n|- bgcolor=#AAFFAA\n|1.\n|align=left|{{wpw|HUN}}\n|'''6'''||3||3||0||0||45|