t": "\u2192\u200etop:fixingSpanish IPAperdiscussion", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ATP_Buenos_Aires"}
{"title_page": "Mauro Z\u00e1rate", "text_new": "{{For|the baseball player|Mauro Z\u00e1rate (baseball)}}  \n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography \n| name                = Mauro Z\u00e1rate \n| image               = Mauro Z\u00e1rate with West Ham in July 2015.jpg \n| image_size          = 200        \n| caption             = Z\u00e1rate playing for [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in 2015 \n| fullname            = Mauro Mat\u00edas Z\u00e1rate<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/408901 |title=Premier League clubs publish retained lists |publisher=Premier League |date=9 June 2017 |accessdate=17 February 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1987|3|13|df=y}}<ref>Birth registered on 18 March 1987, cf. [http://www.lalaziosiamonoi.it/news/allenamenti-speciali-per-zarate-11090 Allenamenti speciali per Zarate, lalaziosiamonoi.it]</ref>\n| birth_place         = [[Haedo, Buenos Aires|Haedo]], Argentina\n| height              = 1.76 m<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/teamsandplayers/players/player=250011652/profile/index.html |title=Mauro Z\u00e1rate |publisher=UEFA |accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/players/profile.html/mauro-zarate |title=Player profile: Mauro Zarate |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=30 December 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6VCg0yxBC?url=http://www.premierleague.com/en-gb/players/profile.html/mauro-zarate |archivedate=30 December 2014}}</ref>\n| position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]], [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]]\n| currentclub         = [[Boca Juniors]]\n| clubnumber          = 19\n| youthyears1         =\n| youthclubs1         = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]]\n| years1              = 2004\u20132007\n| clubs1              = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]]\n| caps1               = 99\n| goals1              = 28\n| years2              = 2007\u20132009\n| clubs2              = [[Al Sadd SC|Al-Sadd]]\n| caps2               = 6\n| goals2              = 4\n| years3              = 2008\n| clubs3              = \u2192 [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] (loan)\n| caps3               = 14\n| goals3              = 4\n| years4              = 2008\u20132009\n| clubs4              = \u2192 [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] (loan)\n| caps4               = 36\n| goals4              = 13\n| years5              = 2009\u20132013\n| clubs5              = [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]\n| caps5               = 68\n| goals5              = 12\n| years6              = 2011\u20132012\n| clubs6              = \u2192 [[Inter Milan]] (loan)\n| caps6               = 22\n| goals6              = 2\n| years7              = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs7              = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]]\n| caps7               = 28\n| goals7              = 18\n| years8              = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs8              = [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]\n| caps8               = 22\n| goals8              = 5\n| years9              = 2015\n| clubs9              = \u2192 [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] (loan)\n| caps9               = 4\n| goals9              = 0\n| years10             = 2016\u20132017\n| clubs10             = [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]\n| caps10              = 22\n| goals10             = 5\n| years11             = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs11             = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]]\n| caps11              = 3\n| goals11             = 0\n| years12             = 2017\n| clubs12             = \u2192 [[Al-Nasr Dubai SC|Al-Nasr]] (loan)\n| caps12              = 8\n| goals12             = 3\n| years13             = 2018\n| clubs13             = \u2192 [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]] (loan)\n| caps13              = 13\n| goals13             = 8\n| years14             = 2018\u2013\n| clubs14             = [[Boca Juniors]]\n| caps14              = 35\n| goals14             = 8\n| nationalyears1      = 2007\n| nationalteam1       = [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina U20]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 5\n| nationalgoals1      = 2\n| club-update         = 23 february 2020\n| nationalteam-update =\n}}\n'''Mauro Mat\u00edas Z\u00e1rate''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8maw\u027eo ma\u02c8ti.as \u02c8sa\u027eate|am}}; born 13 March 1987) is an Argentine [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Boca Juniors]].\n\nZ\u00e1rate started his career with [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]] in his native country, playing three years for the team and winning the [[Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] title in the [[2004\u201305 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n#Torneo Clausura|2005 Clausura tournament]]. He later signed for Qatari side [[Al Sadd SC|Al-Sadd]] in 2007, where he played only six months before transferring on loan to [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] in England. However, after Birmingham's [[Promotion and relegation|relegation]], Z\u00e1rate was loaned out again, this time to [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] in Italy, where he won the [[Coppa Italia]]. His move to Lazio was then made permanent for a fee of around \u20ac20&nbsp;million, with a \u20ac60&nbsp;million<ref name=repubblica/> buy-out clause. After a loan at [[Inter Milan]] and a brief return to V\u00e9lez Sarsfield, he joined [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in 2014, spending the second half of his first season on loan at [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]]. In January 2016, Z\u00e1rate joined Italian club [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]. A year later, he joined [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] of the English [[Premier League]] on a two-and-a-half-year, \u00a32.3&nbsp;million deal.\n\nAt international level, Z\u00e1rate scored the winning goal as the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina under-20 team]] won the [[2007 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] final.\n\n==Club career==\n===V\u00e9lez Sarsfield===\nZ\u00e1rate began his club football career at [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]] where he had played since childhood. At age 17, considered too strong for the youth category, he was promoted to the first team with which he made his full debut on 21 April 2004 against [[Arsenal de Sarand\u00ed]]. He shared the top-scorer award for the [[2006\u201307 in Argentine football|Apertura 2006]] with [[Rodrigo Palacio]] ([[Boca Juniors]]) with 12 goals each.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/clubfootball/news/newsid=108632.html |title=Estudiantes make up for lost time |publisher=FIFA |date=15 December 2006 |accessdate=21 January 2008}}</ref>\n\n===Al-Sadd===\nOn 18 June 2007, Z\u00e1rate signed a two-year deal with Al-Sadd in the [[Qatar National First Division|Qatari League]]<ref>{{cite web\n|title=Al Sadd snare Argentine starlet\n|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/clubfootball/news/newsid=536454.html\n|publisher=FIFA\n|date=16 June 2007\n|accessdate=21 January 2008}}</ref> for a fee reported by ''[[Clar\u00edn (Argentine newspaper)|Clar\u00edn]]'' at $22&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://www.clarin.com/diario/2007/06/17/deportes/d-07401.htm\n|title=Los goles de Z\u00e1rate valen 22 millones de d\u00f3lares\n|work=Clar\u00edn\n|language=Spanish |trans-title=Z\u00e1rate's goals worth $22&nbsp;million\n|author=Tagliaferri, Guillermo\n|date=17 June 2007\n|accessdate=25 February 2008}}</ref> However, he did not remain in Qatar long, playing just six league matches and scoring four goals, before heading on loan to English [[Premier League]] side [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]].\n\n====Birmingham City (loan)====\n[[File:MauroZarate vVilla cropped.jpg|thumb|upright|Z\u00e1rate playing for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] in 2008]]\n\nOn 21 January 2008, Z\u00e1rate joined Premier League side Birmingham City on loan until the end of the [[2007\u201308 Premier League|2007\u201308 season]], with a view to a permanent deal.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/birmingham_city/7200207.stm\n|title=Blues land Argentine star on loan\n|publisher=BBC Sport\n|date=21 January 2008\n|accessdate=21 January 2008}}</ref> He made his debut for the club in the 2\u20130 defeat at [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] on 29 January as a 66th-minute substitute for [[Cameron Jerome]],<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7210578.stm |title=Sunderland 2\u20130 Birmingham |publisher=BBC Sport |author=Lyon, Sam |date=29 January 2008 |accessdate=29 January 2008}}</ref>\nand made his first start on 12 March against [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Hassan|first=Nabil|title=Portsmouth 4\u20132 Birmingham|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7284942.stm|accessdate=29 May 2014|publisher=BBC Sport|date=12 March 2008}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club against [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] on 22 March,<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7298218.stm |title=Reading 2\u20131 Birmingham |publisher=BBC Sport |author=Hughes, Ian |date=22 March 2008 |accessdate=22 March 2008}}</ref> followed by a brace in their next match against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in a 3\u20131 win,<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7309354.stm |title= Birmingham 3\u20131 Man City |publisher=BBC Sport |author=Chowdhury, Saj |date=29 March 2008 |accessdate=30 March 2008}}</ref>\nand a [[direct free kick|free-kick]] that earned a draw against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] on 12 April.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7332036.stm |title= Birmingham 1\u20131 Everton |publisher=BBC Sport |author=Fletcher, Paul |date=12 April 2008 |accessdate=13 April 2008}}</ref>\nAfter a total of 4 goals in 14 matches, Z\u00e1rate left the club at the end of his loan spell, their [[promotion and relegation|relegation]] from the Premier League meaning no extension to the loan would be considered.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.birminghammail.net/birmingham-sport/birmingham-city-fc/birmingham-city-fc-news/2008/05/14/mauro-zarate-signs-off-from-birmingham-city-97319-20907975/ |title=Mauro Zarate signs off from Birmingham City |author=Tattum, Colin |work=Birmingham Mail |date=14 May 2008 |accessdate=14 May 2008}}</ref>\n\n===Lazio===\nZ\u00e1rate completed a move to Italian [[Serie A]] club [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] on 5 July 2008. He joined initially on loan, for \u20ac2.4&nbsp;million,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sslazio.it/images/documents/investors/PROGETTO%20BILANCIO%2030-06-09.pdf |format=PDF |title=Progetto di bilancio al 30 Giugno 2009 |publisher=S.S. Lazio S.p.A.|date=24 September 2008 |page=69 |accessdate=1 January 2017 |quote=Costi per Acquisizione temporanea prestazioni calciatori}}</ref> with Lazio having an option to make the deal permanent,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/birmingham_city/7491793.stm|title=Lazio secure Zarate in loan deal|publisher=BBC Sport|date=5 July 2008|accessdate=6 July 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.al-saddclub.com/output/newspage.aspx?pageID=1340 |title=Al-Sadd okay Zarate loan deal to Lazio |publisher=Al Sadd SC |date=30 June 2008 |accessdate=11 July 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080916222643/http://www.al-saddclub.com/output/newspage.aspx?pageID=1340 |archivedate=16 September 2008}}</ref> and following a successful medical, he was presented to the media a few days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sslazio.it/cms/view/home/news/archivio/elenco_news/zarate_sono_qui_per_vincere_/s152/c1661 |title=Zarate: \"Sono qui per vincere\" |publisher=S.S. Lazio |date=10 July 2008 |accessdate=11 July 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080729000426/http://www.sslazio.it/cms/view/home/news/archivio/elenco_news/zarate_sono_qui_per_vincere_/s152/c1661 |archivedate=29 July 2008 |language=it |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nZ\u00e1rate immediately endeared himself to the Lazio faithful, scoring twice in his Serie A debut against [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] and dedicating the second to the Lazio supporters.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lazio.net/news/2008/08/31/zarate-dedico-la-doppietta-ai-tifosi-corrieredellosportit/ |newspaper=Corriere dello Sport |title=Zarate: \"Dedico la doppietta ai tifosi\" |date=31 August 2008 |accessdate=5 September 2008 |language=it}}</ref> He also scored on his home debut, with a left-footed strike from outside the penalty area against [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]]. This rich goalscoring form continued with Z\u00e1rate scoring once against [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] at the [[San Siro]], twice against [[Torino F.C.|Torino]] and another against [[S.S. Robur Siena|Siena]]. However, by mid-season, Z\u00e1rate hit a dip in form and found himself being substituted for captain [[Tommaso Rocchi]], who was returning to form following serious injury.\n\nOn 28 February, Z\u00e1rate scored both Lazio goals in a 2\u20130 win at the [[Stadio Olimpico|Olimpico]] against [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]]; he became the sixth-highest top scorer in the [[2008\u201309 Serie A]] with ten goals.\n\n[[File:Mauro Zarate and Goran Pandev.jpg|thumb|upright|Z\u00e1rate kicking off the [[2009 Coppa Italia Final]] with [[Goran Pandev]]]]\n\nOn 13 May, Z\u00e1rate won the [[2008\u201309 Coppa Italia|Coppa Italia]] with Lazio, scoring a fourth-minute goal in the 1\u20131 draw with Sampdoria in the [[2009 Coppa Italia Final|final]], as well as a penalty in the victorious shootout.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://goal.com/en/news/10/italy/2009/05/13/1263642/lazio-edge-sampdoria-on-penalties-to-claim-fifth-coppa-italia |title=Lazio Edge Sampdoria on Penalties To Claim Fifth Coppa Italia |date=13 May 2009 |publisher=Goal.com |accessdate=14 May 2009}}</ref> After the season ended, his move to Lazio was made permanent for a fee of approximately \u20ac20&nbsp;million, with a \u20ac60&nbsp;million buy-out clause included in the contract.<ref name=repubblica>{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2009/08/22/zarate-vale-60-milioni-de-silvestri-verso.html|title=Zarate vale 60 milioni. De Silvestri verso Firenze|work=la Repubblica|author=Giulio Cardone|date=22 August 2009|page=14|language=it}}</ref> The [[Italian Football Federation]] (FIGC) later fined Lazio and suspended club president [[Claudio Lotito]] over financial irregularities around the transfer.{{#tag:ref|The [[Italian Football Federation]] (FIGC) later revealed Lazio had to pay an additional \u20ac14.95&nbsp;million to a agent company, Pluriel Limited, whose sole director was [[Riccardo Petrucchi]], in five-year instalments (hidden in agent commission, ({{lang-it|Costi per intermediazione tesserati}})), which Z\u00e1rate's salary was just \u20ac7.2&nbsp;million in net in total in his five-year contract. The FIGC ruled that president Claudio Lotito and Lazio violated the third parties ownership rule in relation to both Z\u00e1rate and [[Julio Ricardo Cruz|Julio Cruz]]. The FIGC suspended Lotito for ten months and fined Lazio \u20ac80,000.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.figc.it/Assets/contentresources_2/ContenutoGenerico/97.$plit/C_2_ContenutoGenerico_31892_StrilloComunicatoUfficiale_lstAllegati_Allegato_0_upfAllegato.pdf |format=PDF |title=Comunicato Ufficiale N.90/CDN (2011\u201312) |date=26 April 2012 |accessdate=1 May 2012 |publisher=FIGC Commissione Disciplinare Nazionale |language=Italian}}</ref>|group=\"nb\"|name=\"Lotito\"}}\n\nZ\u00e1rate caused controversy when he was photographed apparently giving a [[fascist salute]] while watching Lazio lose to [[F.C. Bari 1908|Bari]] in March 2010 among a group of fans, though his spokesman claimed afterwards the player \"did not realise the significance of his gesture\" and did not know who [[Hitler]] or [[Mussolini]] were.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20100320/sport/lazios-player-agent-plays-down-nazi-salute-scandal.299105 |title=Lazio player's agent plays down Nazi-salute scandal |newspaper=The Times of Malta |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=20 March 2010 |accessdate=11 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Z\u00e1rate's transfer was involved in another controversy for solidarity contribution.{{#tag:ref|\nIn July 2010, FIFA's Dispute Resolution Chamber passed a decision that ordered Lazio to pay an additional [[Solidarity Contribution (football)|solidarity contribution]] of \u20ac726,936 owed to V\u00e9lez Sarsfield. Lazio only paid \u20ac73,442.77 corresponding to the \u20ac2.4&nbsp;million loan fee. They rejected Lazio's claim that the club had paid \u20ac20M to Z\u00e1rate, who had then paid Al-Sadd to terminate his contract in April 2009, so that he was signed as a free agent and the \u20ac20&nbsp;million was not a transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/affederation/administration/drcsolidarity/7101224.pdf|title=Decision 7101224 of FIFA Dispute Resolution Chamber |date=22 July 2010 |accessdate=11 May 2011 |publisher=FIFA |format=PDF}}</ref> In February 2011, Lazio appealed, but the appeal was dismissed.<ref>http://www.sslazio.it/images/stories/documenti/pdf/investor_relator/Relazione%2031-03-11%20Lazio%20consolidato_DEF.pdf</ref>|group=\"nb\"|name=\"solidarity \"}}\n\n====Inter Milan (loan)====\nOn 31 August 2011, Z\u00e1rate completed a loan deal from Lazio to [[Inter Milan]] with a view to a permanent transfer.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/clubfootball/news/newsid=1502521.html |title=Inter seal Z\u00e1rate loan deal |publisher=FIFA |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=31 August 2011 |accessdate=31 August 2011}}</ref> On 27 September 2011, he scored a 79th-minute winner, his first goal for the club, in an away match against [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]] in the [[2011\u201312 UEFA Champions League group stage|group stage]] of the [[2011\u201312 UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://fourfourtwo.com/news/championsleague/86659/default.aspx |title=Zarate strike steers Inter to success in Moscow |magazine=FourFourTwo |agency=Reuters |date=27 September 2011 |accessdate=1 October 2011}}</ref> His first Serie A goal for Inter did not come until 1 April 2012, when he scored their fourth goal, a \"spectacular curling right-footed shot\" in a 5\u20134 win against [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]].<ref name=\"AtInter1\">{{cite web | url=http://www.inter.it/en/news/39574 | title=Inter 5\u20134 Genoa: thriller at the Meazza | publisher=Inter Milan | date=1 April 2012 | accessdate=29 May 2014}}</ref> He finished the [[2011\u201312 Inter Milan season|2011\u201312 season]] with 3 goals from 29 appearances in all competitions.<ref name=\"sb1112\">{{Soccerbase season|48560|2011|access-date=29 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n====Lazio return====\nZ\u00e1rate returned to Lazio for the [[2012\u201313 S.S. Lazio season|2012\u201313 season]]. However, he made only five appearances, four in the [[UEFA Europe League]] and one in Serie A, all without scoring, and he did not play for the club after November 2012.<ref name=\"sb1213\">{{Soccerbase season|48560|2012|access-date=29 May 2014}}</ref> In March 2013, he was fined \u20ac500,000 by Lazio \u2013 he had requested time-off to fly home to Argentina to receive treatment for a skin condition, but instead, he flew with his family on a holiday in the [[Maldives]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.football-italia.net/32218/war-between-zarate-and-lazio | title=War between Zarate and Lazio | publisher=football-italia.net | date=23 March 2013 | accessdate=29 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/soccer/hammers-snap-up-zarate-30312958.html | title=Hammers sign Zarate | work=The Irish Independent | date=28 May 2014 | accessdate=29 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n===V\u00e9lez Sarsfield return===\nIn July 2013, Z\u00e1rate returned to his first club, V\u00e9lez Sarsfield,<ref name=\"ReturntoVelez \">{{cite web|url=http://www.teamtalk.com/news/2483/8826482/Mauro-Zarate-slams-Lazio-president-Claudio-Lotito-upon-the-striker-s-exit |title=Zarate slams Lazio president |publisher=Teamtalk.com |date=16 July 2013 |accessdate=21 May 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140521130512/http://www.teamtalk.com/news/2483/8826482/Mauro-Zarate-slams-Lazio-president-Claudio-Lotito-upon-the-striker-s-exit |archivedate=21 May 2014}}</ref> without terminating his contract with Lazio. Consequently, on 2 July 2015, [[FIFA]] ruled Lazio were eligible to receive \u20ac5.26&nbsp;million in compensation, which V\u00e9lez and Z\u00e1rate were jointly liable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sslazio.it/images/stories/documenti/pdf/investor_relator/Bilancio%20S.S.%20LAZIO%20SpA%20al%2030-06-2015%20-%20app.7-10-15.pdf|title=BILANCIO AL 30 GIUGNO 2015|date=7 October 2015|access-date=8 October 2015|publisher=S.S. Lazio|language=Italian}}</ref> In January 2014, Z\u00e1rate was a member of the side which won the [[2013 Supercopa Argentina]], beating Arsenal de Sarand\u00ed 1\u20130 in the final.<ref name=\"2014supercopa\">{{cite web | url=http://www.eltiempo.com/archivo/documento/CMS-13440095 | title=V\u00e9lez Sarsfield gan\u00f3 la Supercopa Argentina | publisher=eltiempo.com | date=1 February 2014 | accessdate=29 May 2014 | language=Spanish}}</ref> He finished the season as top scorer in [[2013\u201314 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n season#Torneo Final|Primera Divisi\u00f3n Torneo Final]] with 13 goals in 19 matches.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.espnfc.com/player/_/id/69133/mauro-z%C3%A1rate?cc=3436 | title=Mauro Z\u00e1rate | publisher=ESPN | accessdate=29 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=whusign/>\n\n===West Ham United===\n[[File:Mauro Zarate signing autographs at the Boleyn Ground October 2014.jpg|thumb|upright|Z\u00e1rate signing autographs at the [[Boleyn Ground]] in 2014]]\n\nOn 28 May 2014, Z\u00e1rate signed a three-year contract with Premier League club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] to take effect when the international transfer window opened in June.<ref name=whusign>{{cite web |url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2014/may/28-may/zarate-signs |title=Zarate signs |publisher=West Ham United F.C. |date=28 May 2014 |accessdate=5 May 2017}}</ref> On 23 August, he scored on his competitive debut for the club, opening a 3\u20131 win away to [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] with a 20-yard volley.<ref>[http://www.whufc.com/articles/20140823/zarate-enjoys-dream-debut_2236884_4093549 Zarate enjoys dream debut | West Ham United] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140825011911/http://www.whufc.com/articles/20140823/zarate-enjoys-dream-debut_2236884_4093549 |date=25 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n====Queens Park Rangers (loan)====\nOn 6 January 2015, Z\u00e1rate was loaned to fellow Premier League club [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] until the end of [[2014\u201315 Queens Park Rangers F.C. season|the season]], having scored two goals in eight matches for West Ham.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mauro Zarate: West Ham striker joins QPR on loan|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30697682|accessdate=6 January 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=6 January 2015}}</ref> Having made four appearances for QPR without scoring, in May 2015, Z\u00e1rate reacted angrily to being omitted from the squad for a match against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]. His actions were deemed bad enough by the club that he was ordered to make his own way back to London and was subsequently banned and fined two weeks' wages. Such was the length of the ban, coinciding with the end of the season, this effectively ended his QPR career.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/chelsea-close-to-wrapping-up-2m-deal-for-rob-green-as-petr-cech-replacement-10243888.html | title=Chelsea close to wrapping up \u00a32m deal for Rob Green as Petr Cech replacement | work=London Evening Standard | date=12 May 2015 | accessdate=12 May 2015 | author=Johnson, Simon}}</ref>\n\n====West Ham United return====\nZ\u00e1rate featured in West Ham's [[2015\u201316 UEFA Europa League]] qualifying campaign in pre-season, scoring his first goal of the season in a 2\u20132 draw at the [[Boleyn Ground]] against Romanian club [[FC Astra Giurgiu|Astra Giurgiu]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11685/9930047/west-ham-xxxx-fc-astra | title=West Ham 2\u20132 FC Astra: Enner Valencia injured and James Collins sent off for Hammers | publisher=Sky Sports | accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref> West Ham eventually lost the tie 3\u20134 after a narrow second leg defeat.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33738588 | title=Astra 2\u20131 West Ham | publisher=BBC Sport | accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nZ\u00e1rate scored from outside the penalty area to conclude West Ham's 2\u20130 win over [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] at the [[Emirates Stadium]] in their opening match game of the [[2015\u201316 Premier League|2015\u201316 Premier League season]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Osborne|first1=Chris|title=Arsenal 0\u20132 West Ham|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33750502|accessdate=9 August 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 August 2015}}</ref> His deflected strike could not save West Ham from third round elimination in the [[2015\u201316 Football League Cup|2015\u201316 League Cup]], [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] prevailing 2\u20131 after extra time.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34253542 | title=Leicester 2\u20131 West Ham | publisher=BBC Sport | accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref> He continued his good early season scoring form as he scored the opening goal in the ''Hammers''' 2\u20131 victory over [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] on 24 October, following this up with a free-kick in a televised match against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] on 29 November, a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34558482 | title=West Ham 2\u20131 Chelsea | publisher=BBC Sport | accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34893456 | title=West Ham 1\u20131 West Brom | publisher=BBC Sport | accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Fiorentina===\nOn 21 January 2016, Z\u00e1rate completed a move to Italian club [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] for an undisclosed fee,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/35378300|title=Mauro Zarate: West Ham striker joins Fiorentina|publisher=BBC Sport|date=21 January 2016|accessdate=21 January 2016}}</ref> reported by [[Sky Sports]] to be \u00a31.6&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Mauro Zarate leaves West Ham to join Fiorentina |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11685/10138717/mauro-zarate-leaves-west-ham-to-join-fiorentina |first=Nick |last=Lustig |publisher=Sky Sports |date=22 January 2016 |access-date=22 January 2016}}</ref> He made his debut for ''La Viola'' ten days later, starting in their goalless draw at Genoa. On 3 February, he scored his first goal for the team, the last-minute winner in a 2\u20131 victory over [[Carpi F.C. 1909|Carpi]] at the [[Stadio Artemio Franchi]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mauro Zarate makes the difference with late winner for Fiorentina against Carpi|url=http://www.espnfc.com/italian-serie-a/match/432042/fiorentina-carpi/report|accessdate=23 February 2016|agency=Press Association|publisher=ESPN|date=3 February 2016}}</ref> However, 11 days later, he was sent off in a win by the same score against Inter for grabbing at [[Jeison Murillo]]; he subsequently received a three-match ban.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gladwell|first1=Ben|title=Fiorentina's Mauro Zarate shocked by three-match ban for red card|url=http://www.espnfc.com/fiorentina/story/2809525/fiorentina-forward-mauro-zarate-shocked-by-three-match-ban|accessdate=23 February 2016|publisher=ESPN|date=17 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Watford===\nOn 25 January 2017, Z\u00e1rate joined Premier League side [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] on a two-and-a-half-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |title=Z\u00e1rate Signs For Hornets |url=https://www.watfordfc.com/teams/first-team/zarate-signs-hornets |publisher=Watford F.C. |date=25 January 2017 |accessdate=25 January 2017}}</ref> On 25 February, he won a penalty in a game against his former club West Ham, but later injured [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|his cruciate ligament]] after twisting his knee awkwardly. Z\u00e1rate needed nine minutes of medical attention and would likely miss the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/watford/story/3069458/watford-winger-mauro-zarate-suffers-cruciate-ligament-damage-against-west-ham|title=Watford winger Mauro Zarate confirms cruciate ligament damage|work=PA Sports|publisher=ESPN FC|date=26 February 2017|accessdate=27 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Al-Nasr (loan)====\nOn 2 October 2017, Z\u00e1rate joined United Arab Emirati club [[Al-Nasr Dubai SC|Al-Nasr]] in a loan deal slated to run until the end of the 2017\u201318 season.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Mauro Zarate leaves Watford on loan to UAE side Al Nasr | publisher = Sky Sports | date = 2 October 2017 | accessdate = 6 June 2018 | url = http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11686/11064437/mauro-zarate-leaves-watford-on-loan-to-uae-side-al-nasr}}</ref> After failing to find the net in his first four games, he then scored three goals in as many games for the [[UAE Pro-League]] club.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Loan Lads {{!}} Z\u00e1rate Strikes Again | author = | publisher = Watford F.C. | date = 6 December 2017 | accessdate = 6 July 2018 | url = https://www.watfordfc.com/teams/first-team/loan-lads-zarate-strikes-again}}</ref>\n\n====V\u00e9lez Sarsfield (loan)====\nIn January 2018, after eight appearances for Al-Nasr, it was announced that Z\u00e1rate had rejoined V\u00e9lez Sarsfield on loan, for his third spell at the club where he started his career.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Velez confirm Zarate loan | last = Storey | first = Matt | work = Hertfordshire Mercury | date = 5 January 2018 | accessdate = 6 July 2018 | url = https://www.hertfordshiremercury.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/velez-sarsfield-confirm-loan-signing-1014342}}</ref>\n\n===Boca Juniors===\nIn July 2018, Z\u00e1rate signed for [[Boca Juniors]], despite previously indicating his intention to sign permanently with Velez.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Mauro Zarate accused of stabbing brother in back after transfer U-turn | first = Ed | last = Malyon | work = The Independent | date = 4 July 2018 | accessdate = 6 July 2018 | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/transfer-news-watford-mauro-zarate-brother-boca-juniors-velez-a8428736.html}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nIn 2007, Z\u00e1rate helped the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina national under-20 team]] win the [[2007 FIFA U-20 World Cup]], scoring the winning goal in the final against the [[Czech Republic national under-20 football team|Czech Republic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/u20worldcup/canada2007/news/newsid=557097.html |title=A sixth star for Argentina |publisher=FIFA |date=22 July 2007 |accessdate=1 October 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090214103626/http://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/u20worldcup/canada2007/news/newsid%3D557097.html |archivedate=14 February 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, [[Diego Maradona]] was appointed manager of the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]] and said that if Z\u00e1rate's good form continued, he would get a chance with that team.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/585/argentina/2008/12/28/1031695/maradona-commends-zarate-embraces-cambiasso |title=Maradona commends Zarate, embraces Cambiasso |publisher=Goal.com |date=28 December 2008 |accessdate=6 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Z\u00e1rate opted to play international football for [[Chile national football team|Chile]] after not being named in the latest Argentina squad chosen by manager [[Gerardo Martino]]. He is eligible for the country through his father.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://golazoargentino.wordpress.com/2014/10/30/west-hams-zarate-chooses-chile-over-argentina/ | title=West Ham's Zarate chooses Chile over Argentina | publisher=Golazoargentina | date=30 October 2014 | accessdate=30 October 2014}}</ref> However, in 2015, Z\u00e1rate expressly stated he is Argentine and has always dreamt of playing for Argentina.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.ole.com.ar/futbol-internacional/argentino_0_1456054591.html |publisher=Ol\u00e9 |language=Spanish |title=Soy argentino |date=26 October 2015 |accessdate=26 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nZ\u00e1rate was born in [[Haedo, Buenos Aires]], to a footballing family. His father Sergio is a [[Chilean people|Chilean]] former professional footballer who played for [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Independiente|Independiente de Avellaneda]]. His mother, Catalina Riga, has Italian origins from [[Catanzaro]] in southern Italy. His grandfather Juvenal was Chilean and also a footballer.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lazio.net/news/2008/06/30/zarate-una-generazione-di-calciatori-corrieredellosport/ |title=Zarate, una generazione di calciatori [The Zarates, a generation of footballers]|format=reprint |first=Daniele |last=Rindone |newspaper=Corriere dello Sport |date=30 June 2008 |publisher=Lazio.net |accessdate=10 June 2011 |language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lanacion.com.ar/5484 |title=Z\u00e1rate: goles argentinos para las penas del Real Madrid [Z\u00e1rate: Argentine goals for Real Madrid fans] |newspaper=La Naci\u00f3n |location=Argentina |date=16 February 2000 |accessdate=10 June 2011 |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.puntosport.net/pageview2.php?i=21549&sl=1 |title=Zarate, futuro Italia? L'ipotesi \u00e8 suggestiva [Zarate, Italy in the future? The hypothesis is suggestive] |date=11 November 2009 |publisher=PuntoSport |accessdate=10 June 2011 |language=Italian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008015328/http://www.puntosport.net/pageview2.php?i=21549&sl=1 |archivedate=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n\nMauro is the youngest brother of former footballers [[Rolando Z\u00e1rate|Rolando]] and [[Ariel Silvio Z\u00e1rate|Ariel]], as well as former international [[Sergio Z\u00e1rate|Sergio]], who acts as Mauro's agent.<ref>{{cite news|title=Extorsionan a una familia de futbolistas y les balean una casa\n|url=http://www.clarin.com/diario/2006/08/10/policiales/g-04801.htm|publisher=Clar\u00edn|language=Spanish|date=10 August 2006}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{Updated|19 April 2019}}<ref>{{soccerway|mauro-zarate/22236|accessdate=17 March 2019}}</ref>{{citation needed|date=October 2018|reason=Soccerway doesn't verify Velez stats for first spell}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]]\n|[[2003\u201304 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2003\u201304]]\n||[[Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]\n|5||1||0||0||0||0||5||1\n|-\n|[[2004\u201305 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2004\u201305]]\n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n\n|14||2||0||0||0||0||14||2\n|-\n|[[2005\u201306 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2005\u201306]]\n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n\n|24||3||0||0||12||3||36||6\n|-\n|[[2006\u201307 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2006\u201307]]\n|Primera Divisi\u00f3n\n|32||16||0||0||12||3||44||19\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!75!!22!!0!!0!!24!!6!!99!!28\n|-\n|[[Al Sadd SC|Al Saad]]\n|[[2007-08 Qatar Stars Leag