{"title_page": "2006 Women's European Water Polo Championship", "text_new": "The '''[[European Water Polo Championship|2006 Women's European Water Polo Championship]]''' was the eleventh edition of the now tri-annual event, organised by the Europe's governing body in aquatics, the [[Ligue Europ\u00e9enne de Natation]]. The event took place in the [[Banjica Sports Center]] in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]] from September 2 to September 9, 2006.\n\nThere were two [[2006 Women's European Water Polo Championship Qualifier|qualification tournaments]] ahead of the event, held from April 7 to April 9, 2006 in [[Nancy, France]] (with France, Germany, Great Britain and the Netherlands competing) and in [[Madrid, Spain]] (Czech Republic, Greece, Spain and Ukraine).\n\n==Qualification==\n*{{further|2006 Women's European Water Polo Championship Qualifier}}\n\n==Teams==\n{{col-begin-small}}\n{{col-2}}\n;GROUP A\n*{{wpw|HUN}} \n*{{wpw|NED}}\n*{{wpw|SRB}} \n*{{wpw|ESP}} \n{{col-2}}\n;GROUP B\n*{{wpw|GER}} \n*{{wpw|GRE}}\n*{{wpw|ITA}} \n*{{wpw|RUS}} \n{{col-end}}\n\n==Squads==\n\n==={{wpw|GER}}===\n{{col-begin-small}}\n{{col-3}}\n*[[Simone Budde]]\n*[[Lina Rohe]]\n*[[Linda Gerritsen]]\n*[[Ariane Rump]]\n*[[Katrin Dierolf]]\n*[[Claudia Blomenkamp]]\n{{col-3}}\n*[[Monika Kruszona]]\n*[[Nadine Kunz]]\n*[[Theresa Klein]]\n*[[Nina Wengst]]\n*[[Sabrina Blattau]]\n*[[Mandy Z\u00f6llner]]\n{{col-3}}\n*[[Claudia Sch\u00f6nitz]]\n'''Head Coach''':\n*[[Bernd Seidensticher]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==={{wpw|GRE}}===\n{{col-begin-small}}\n{{col-3}}\n*[[Alexandra Asimaki]]\n*[[Alkisti Avramidou]]\n*[[Christina Dimitrokali]]\n*[[Angeliki Gerolymou]]\n*[[Konstantina Kouteli]]\n*[[Triantafyllia Manolioudaki]]\n{{col-3}}\n*[[Vasileia Mavrelou]]\n*[[Stella Mitsani]]\n*[[Kelina Kantzou]]\n*[[Sofia Iosifidou]]\n*[[Stavroula Kozompoli]]\n*[[Georgia Lara]]\n{{col-3}}\n*[[Maria Tsouri]]\n*[[Anastasia Zervakaki]]\n*[[Marieta Zilakou]]\n'''Head Coach''':\n*[[Kyriakos Iosifidis]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==={{wpw|HUN}}===\n{{col-b